Stranded

by: Stefanie Back

This game was made for my level 2 project at The League of Amazing Programmers.
Click here to download and play!

1. Why I Made This Game

It was not too different from the original League Invader program that I coded.

2. What I Learned

I should not make the human fly around the screen(I made it so that the player could only go side to side).

3. Architecture of My Game

There are 7 different classes: GamePanel, GameObject, Falling_Fruit, Human, ObjectManager, Projectile(Which is all commented and never got deleted), and Stranded(which is the main platform for the game). Falling_Fruit was originally aliens from the League Invader program, Human was also originally rocketship, and same with Stranded, which was originally LeagueInvaders.

4. Technical Implementation

I am proud that I was able to make it so that once three strawberries fall, the game ends. Also, getting the images to work was a huge accomplishment, because there were many failed attempts at finding the right images.

5. Most Challenging Part

The most challenging part was when the game stopped after one strawberry. I soon found out that it was a quite simple problem. I had help from my teacher finding where the problem was, but I eventually fixed it.

6. Future Fixes and Updates

I would make it so that if someone survived long enough, a boat would come after them and save them.
